<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation: (a) "unginned cotton" means the fruit of the cotton plant (Gossypium) which has reached maturity and been harvested and which contains pod and leaf fragments and soil matter; </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamisel kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: a) toorpuuvill - puuvillap&otilde;&otilde;sa (Gossypium) k&uuml;psed ja koristatud viljad, sisaldab kuprakesti, lehti ja mullataolisi osakesi; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) "ginned cotton" means cotton fibres (other than linters and waste), neither carded nor combed, from which the seeds and most of the pod and leaf fragments and soil matter have been removed. </inglise>
<eesti> b) puuvillakiud - kraasimata ja kammimata puuvillakiud (muud kui puuvillaebemed ja j&auml;&auml;tmed), millest on eemaldatud seemned ja enamik kuprakestadest, lehtedest ja mullataolistest osakestest. </eesti>
